@startuml
' =============================================================================
' Architecture definition for the ArchUnit demo project.
'
' This diagram is the SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for allowed layer dependencies.
' ArchUnit's PlantUmlArchCondition reads this file at test time and enforces
' that actual Java class dependencies match the arrows drawn here.
'
' How to read:
'   [A] --> [B]    means classes in layer A are ALLOWED to depend on layer B.
'   No arrow       means the dependency is FORBIDDEN (test fails if it exists).
'
' Stereotypes (<<..name..>>) map each component to a Java package pattern.
' The ".." wildcards work like ArchUnit's resideInAPackage("..name..") rule.
'
' Editing workflow:
'   1. Draw a new arrow here to allow a new cross-layer dependency.
'   2. Commit the .puml file — no Java rule changes needed.
'   3. The ArchUnit test automatically picks up the updated diagram.
' =============================================================================

[Controller] <<..controller..>>
[Service]    <<..service..>>
[Repository] <<..repository..>>
[Model]      <<..model..>>

[Controller] --> [Service]
[Controller] --> [Model]
[Service]    --> [Repository]
[Service]    --> [Model]
[Repository] --> [Model]

@enduml
